         <entry xml:id="alteksiyya-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#alon-dlgenr"
                next="#alio-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אלטיכסייה</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾlṭyksyyh</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">alṭeksiyyah</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">f</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">תכסיס אלטומסין</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="K" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">תכסיס אלטימסיון</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <form type="equivalent" opt="false">
               <quote xml:lang="grc">ἀλήθεια + ἀξία (Levy I: 83) (?) *αὐλιταξία</quote>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="alteksiyya-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
<!-- working hypothesis: every attestation / example pertains to one sense; so it is nested into it. If there is only one sense, there won't be a number displayed. -->
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>"dignified truth“ (?) or "corps of court guards“ (?)
         </quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example">
<!-- here we have a passage with various readings. Manuscript sigla are provided in the @wit attribute. We have to look how well mixed content works with RTL scripts. -->
                  <quote xml:lang="jpa">
            מה עשה הקב"ה נטל אמת והשליכה לארץ, אמרו מלאכי השרת לפני הקב"ה רבון העולמים מה את מבזה אלטיכסייה שלך, תעלה אמת מן הארץ ה"ה אמת מארץ תצמח.
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">8,5</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 60:9</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation">
                     <quote xml:lang="en">
What did the Holy One, blessed be He? He took the truth and threw it 
on the ground. Said the ministering angels before the Holy One, blessed be He: 
“Sovereign of the universe! Why do you despise your dignified truth / corps of the court guards? Shall the truth arise from the earth! This is what is written: Let truth spring up from the earth (Ps 85,12).
            </quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">=
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq. Ps. 834 [470b: 17]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">תכסיס אלתמסו[י]ן</term>)
         </note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="compounding" subtype="endocentric" opt="false">
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <form opt="false">
                     <orth opt="false">αὐλή</orth>
                  </form>
               </cit>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <form opt="false">
                     <orth opt="false">τάξις</orth>
                  </form>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
      Gloss in <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">BM</bibl>: <term xml:lang="jpa">חותם אמת</term> („seal of truth“). <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq Ps 834 (939: 17)</bibl>: <term xml:lang="jpa">תכסיס אלתמסון</term> emended to <term xml:lang="jpa">אלטיכסייא תכסיס</term> (cf. AC). It is not clear whether the form <term xml:lang="jpa">אלטומסיון</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾlṭwmsywn</term> or <term xml:lang="jpa">אלתמסון</term> (<term xml:lang="jpa">אלטומסין</term>) <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾltmswn</term> (<term xml:lang="fjb">ʾlṭwmsyn</term>) is a corruption of <term xml:lang="jpa">אלטיכסייה</term> or an alternative reading (cf. MY ad loc.). <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 90b</bibl>: <term xml:lang="jpa">אלטיכסייא</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾlṭyksyyʾ</term>
               <term xml:lang="rabbinic">aleṭeyakhsiyya</term> Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἀλήθεια τάξις</term>. <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 68ab</bibl> reads <term xml:lang="jpa">אלטכסיסין</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾlṭksysyn</term>, “chief of the court ceremonies”. <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Bacher (1896) 441 (note 3)</bibl> suggests simply Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἀλήθεια</term>. For the reading of <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq.</bibl> see <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Krauss (1937) 25a</bibl>: Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">τάξις ἀλλαξίμον</term>. Ibid. 425a emends to <term xml:lang="jpa">אלטובסיא</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">ʾlṭwbsyʾ</term> Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἀλήθευσις</term> (this is also the suggestion of <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Schlatter [1900] 50-51</bibl>, cf. <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Sperber, Cards</bibl>).
      <ref type="entry">תכסיס</ref>.
   </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Krauss II</title>
                  <citedRange>53</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
